(1)
the stated interest rate represents the weighted-average coupon rate for each category of borrowings. for floating rate borrowings, interest rates are based upon the rates at
september30, 2006; these rates are not necessarily an indication of future interest rates.
(2)
amounts represent notional values of interest rate and cross-currency swaps.
(3)
the effective interest rate includes only the impact of interest rate and cross-currency swaps on the stated rate of interest. other adjustments to the stated interest rate such as
purchase accounting adjustments and debt issuance costs did not have a material impact on the overall effective interest rate.
(4)
